directions: Drain and rinse black beans
Dump everything in the crockpot/instant poot including the frozen chicken

Cook on high for 3-4 hours or low for 6-8 hours if in crockpot;

Set instant pot to manual pressure for 10 minutes. Natural release for about 5 minutes the release remaining pressure.
Shred the chicken and serve over tortillas
title: Crockpot/Instant Pot Chicken Tacos

directions: Boil the hot dogs
Start the Chili
Eat
title: Chili Dogs

ingredients: 5oz bag of frozen peas and carrots
5oz bag of frozen sweet kernel corn
directions: Rinse the jasmine rice thoroughly until the water draining is clear.
Add water and set instant pot on high pressure for 3 minutes. Natural release for 10 minutes and then quick release the remaining pressure. Remove rice and set aside
Set instant pot to saute. Add the oil and once it's sizzling add the onion. Cook for a minute then add peas, carrots, corn, and butter. Cook for about 2 mintues.
Move the veggies to one side and add the eggs to the other. Constantly stir the eggs and once they begin to cook mix with the veggies.
Add the rice and soy sauce to the instant pot. Stir then serve.
title: Chicken Fried Rice with Jasmine Rice

directions: Preheat the oven to 350. Slice the chicken into strips
Mix the soup mix, dressing, and preserves in a 9x13, then add chicken and cover with sauce
Cook the chicken for 30 minutes in the mixture
Serve over rice
title: Sweet and Sour Chicken

directions: Rinse the rice thoroughly
Add the rice and water in the instant pot. Set to manual high pressure for 8 minutes. Let it natual release the pressure
title: Instant Pot White Rice

directions: Cut pork into 2-inch slices.
Combine brown sugar, chili powder, paprika, salt, pepper, and mustard into a dry rub. Cover cut pork in dry rub.
Set instant pot on saute and add oil. Once oil is hot sear each side of the pork
Add broth, vinegar, and liquid smoke to the cooker. Cook on High for 100 minutes.
Natural release for 15 minutes, the quick release
Remove pork from pot and drain the liquid. Add the bbq sauce and heat until simmering.
Shred the pork and then add back into the instant pot. Stir in sauce and serve.
title: Pulled Pork in the Instant Pot

directions: Set instant pot to saute and add olive oil. Season beef with pepper. Brown meat in instant pot and transfer to a plate when browned. Slice the meat into strips and set aside
Add onions and saute until they start to be soft. Add garlic and saute for another minute.
Add beef broth, soy sauce, brown sugar, sesame oil, and red pepper to the pot. Stir until the sugar is dissolved.
Add sliced beef to instant pot. Set to high pressure for 12 minutes. Quick release pressure once it"s finished.
While instant pot is going, cook broccoli until tender.
Combine cornstarch and water. Once the instant pot is done, set to saute and add cornstarch mixture. Stir until sauce thickens. Add broccoli.
Serve over rice.
title: Beef and Broccoli

ingredients: 1 large white or yellow onion finely diced
1 red bell pepper, seeded and finely diced
1 yellow bell pepper, seeded and finely diced
1 whole chicken, roasted and cooked (rotisserie chicken works too)
1 10.5 oz can of cream of chicken soup
1 10.5 oz can of cream of mushroom soup
1 10 oz can of diced tomatoes and chilies
directions: Preheat oven to 350. Butter 9x13 baking dish
Prep all veggies in a small bowl.
In a bowl combine soups and diced tomatoes and chilies
Add chili powder, cumin, cayenne, salt, black powder, and chicken broth into soup mixture and stir together
Line the bottom of the pan with half of the torn tortillas
Tear cooked chicken into chunks. Add half of the chicken to the dish
Add half of veggie mixture and half of the cheeses to the dish. Then cover with half of the soup mixture.
Repeat with the rest of the ingredients, first tortillas, then chicken, veggies, cheeses, and soup mixture.
Cover with foil and bake for 45 minutes. Then uncover and cook for another 15 minutes or until bubbling.
title: King Ranch Chicken

directions: Add everything except whey protein and ice. Blend until the okra is broken down.
Add the ice and blend until smooth. (Half at a time)
Add the whey protein and blend. Add sweetener to taste.
title: Secret Big Boy - FP

ingredients: 2 cans black beans, rinsed and drained
1 can rotel style diced tomatoes and green chilies
directions: Pour everything into instant pot. High pressure for 12ish minutes
You can serve with some crumbled corn chips or 0% greek yogurt for an E.
To cook chicken breasts in the instant pot, add 2 cups chicken broth and the chicken. High pressure for 6 minutes for thawed chicken, 8 for frozen. Natural release for 5 minutes.
title: Chicken Fiesta Soup - E (THT pg 151)

ingredients: 3/4 cup unsweetened nut milk or coffee
Ice Cubes (number depends on desired thickness)
directions: Place all ingredients in a blender and blend until smooth.
title: Peanut Butter Cup Protein Shake

directions: Preheat the oven to 400. Add 12 cupcake liners and spray with coconut oil cooking spray
Combine the dry ingredients in a large bowl and whisk together. Add the wet ingredients and stir well. Rest for 10 minutes for it to thicken up (it"ll be wet ;) )
Add the batter to the cupcake liners. Bake for 22 minutes.
Add all syrup ingredients in a small saucepan. Set to medium-high heat and bring to a boil, whisking often. Simmer and whisk for a few minutes. Remove from heat.
After the muffins come out, drizzle with the syrup.
title: Peanut Butter Cookie Muffins (FP)
